# Disabled buttons

When a button is disabled, always add a **tooltip** that explains why:

- Use the `title` attribute so users see the reason on hover.
- Set `title` only when the button is disabled (e.g. `title={disabled ? 'Reason here' : undefined}`) so the tooltip does not appear when the button is enabled.

Example:

```tsx
<button
  disabled={loading}
  title={loading ? 'Loadingâ€¦' : undefined}
>
  Submit
</button>
```

For accessibility, prefer also updating `aria-label` when disabled to include the reason (e.g. "Submit (disabled: loading)").
